t: Maschil of David; A Prayer when he was in the cave.
I*p cried unto the Lord*s with my voice; with my voice unto the Lord*s did I make my supplication.
I*p poured out my complaint before him; I shewed before him my trouble.
When*p my spirit was overwhelmed within me, then thou knewest my path. In the way wherein I walked have they privily laid a snare for me.
I*p looked on my right hand, and beheld, but there was no man that would know me: refuge failed me; no man cared for my soul.
I*p cried unto thee, O Lord:*s I said, Thou art my refuge and my portion in the land of the living.
Attend*p unto my cry; for I am brought very low: deliver me from my persecutors; for they are stronger than I.
Bring*p my soul out of prison, that I may praise thy name: the righteous shall compass me about; for thou shalt deal bountifully with me.
